Biography

2022-23: Appeared in all 28 games for the Tigers, starting in three... Scored a season-high six points against Southern Nazarene... Handed out a season high nine assists against NWOSU, the most by a Tiger in a single game since 2017.

2021-22: Appeared in all 28 games and started in four... Averaged 2.9 points on 17.5 minutes... scored a season-high eight points against Southeastern Oklahoma... Third on team in three-point percentage (36.5%).

2020-21: Played in all 17 games, with 11 starts... Made his collegiate debut with five assists at Harding on January 7... Scored a career-high 13 points at Arkansas Tech in the first round of the GAC Tournament.

AT ROSMINI: Two-time National Champion... Captain for the New Zealand National Team in 2018... Competed for the New Zealand 18U team in the 2019 3-on-3 Asia Cup in Malaysia... Led his high school team to the 2019 ISF Basketball World Schools Championships in Greece... Also lettered in golf, bowling and men's volleyball.

PERSONAL: Son of Channon Williams and Audrey Dunn... Has four siblings, Rylie, Pheonix, Kodee and Logan... Majoring in Business Management... Born May 28, 2001.
